data.value:
SAM Suza Help Desk is a small project built by three Computer Science degree students using basic principles of software engineering. The software is based around the SUZA IT help desk at the main campus which lends equipment to both students and lecturers.
With this app, users can:
- Add, edit and delete available items in stock - Keep track of who borrows which items and when they are returned - Instantly know how many of each item are still in stock - Print reports of items in stock and records of borrowing
Built by Seif, Ali Foum and Masanja, April 6, 2021.
